mathwrap
========

A shared library wrapper for 32-bit and 64-bit x86 Linux systems
to redirect calls to math functions from the system libm to bundled
SSE or AVX optimized versions or from external math libraries.

Installation
============

This packages is Linux x86 specific and requires the following tools
to be installed:
- GNU make
- GNU C-compiler (tested with 4.5.1)
- AMD LibM (optional, tested with v3.0)
- Intel SVML (optional, tested with the version bundled with icc 11.1) 

To compile simply type "make". This should produce two
libraries libmathwrap.so and libmathwrap.a.

